#: ../../geovista/docs/src/developer/documentation.rst:348
msgid ""
"A label should be prefixed with ``gv-`` to indicate inclusion within the "
"``geovista`` namespace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/developer/documentation.rst:350
msgid ""
"The ``gv-`` prefix should then be followed by the name of the file "
"containing the label, with hyphens replacing spaces and special characters, "
"and all characters in lower case e.g., ``gv-next-steps`` for the "
":bash:`docs/src/next_steps.rst` document. Include the sub-directory "
"structure in the label if the file is not in the :bash:`docs/src` directory,"
" e.g., ``gv-developer-towncrier`` for the "
":bash:`docs/src/developer/towncrier.rst` document."
msgstr ""

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/developer/documentation.rst:357
msgid ""
"If appropriate, the label should then be followed by the title of the "
"section or subsection it's referencing, with hyphens replacing spaces and "
"special characters, and all characters in lower case e.g., ``gv-developer-"
"documentation-cross-references`` for the :ref:`gv-developer-documentation-"
"cross-references` section in this ``docs/src/developer/documentation.rst`` "
"document. If the label doesn't proceed a section or subsection title, then "
"use a suitable description that is concise and uniquely identifies the "
"location within the document. Avoid using abbreviations or acronyms unless "
"strictly necessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../geovista/docs/src/developer/documentation.rst:370
msgid ""
"A label prefixed with ``tippy-gv-`` instead of ``gv-`` will have a `sphinx-"
"tippy`_ tooltip rendered for each of its cross-reference links e.g., hover "
